Privacy Policy
App: DigiCamFX Photo Filters
Effective Date: March 16, 2026
DigiCamFX Photo Filters ("the App") respects your privacy.
1. Data We Collect
We do not collect, store, transmit, or share personal data from users.
2. Photo Library Access
The App may request access to your Photo Library so you can:

Select photos to edit
Save edited photos back to your library

Photo editing is performed on your device. We do not upload your photos to our servers.
3. Subscriptions and Payments
The App offers auto-renewable subscriptions (weekly and yearly).
All payments and subscription processing are handled by Apple through StoreKit and the App Store.
We do not receive your full payment card details.
Apple may process purchase-related data according to Apple's own privacy policy.
4. Third-Party Services
The App does not use third-party analytics SDKs, ad networks, or tracking tools for user profiling.
5. Data Retention and Deletion
Because we do not collect personal data on our servers, we do not retain server-side personal data and therefore have no server-side personal data to delete.
6. Children's Privacy
The App is not intended to collect personal information from children, and we do not knowingly collect such information.
7. Your Choices
You can manage or revoke Photo Library permission at any time in:
iOS Settings > Privacy & Security > Photos > DigiCamFX Photo Filters
You can manage or cancel subscriptions in:
iOS Settings > [your name] > Subscriptions
8. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The "Effective Date" above will reflect the latest version.
